{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"067a999e4fe5fdf00e1dee21b23a01a3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `domain/glossary.ts` is more sophisticated — it imports from `./odu-data` (which is the empty stub `getOduByName` returns null). So this one also returns null in production.\n\nThe real fix: the `domain/odu-data.ts` `getOduByName` function is a stub returning null. The `glossary.ts` is well-architected but depends on this stub.\n\nPlan: enhance `apps/akasha-portal/src/lib/domain/odu-data.ts` to actually look up real Odu data from `ODUS_IFA` (canonical source). This will:\n- Make `domain/glossary.ts` return real data (it was already correctly architected, just depended on a stub)\n- Make `application/akasha/glossary.ts` redundant but still works (fallback stub)\n\nWait — but the `application/akasha/glossary.ts` is a separate stub. The `daily-engine.ts` and `manifesto-builder.ts` use it (not the domain one). Let me check what's the right place.\n\nLooking at the `consult/route.ts` (line 8): imports from `@/lib/domain/glossary` \nLooking at `daily-engine.ts` and `manifesto-builder.ts`: import from `./glossary` (relative to akasha/)\n\nSo the daily content + manifesto use the application/akasha one, and consult uses domain. Both stubs.\n\nBest approach:\n1. Fix `domain/odu-data.ts` `getOduByName` to return real data from `ODUS_IFA`\n2. The `domain/glossary.ts` will then automatically work correctly (no change needed)\n3. Fix `application/akasha/glossary.ts` `buildOduGlossary` to also use real data (either by deriving from ODUS_IFA directly, or by importing from domain/glossary)\n4. Add a test\n\nActually, looking again — `domain/odu-data.ts` has its own `OduData` interface with fields like `id`, `name`, `meaning`, `verses`, `element`, `quizilas`, `preceitos`, `essencia`, `元素`. This is different shape from `ODUS_IFA`. So I need to either:\nA. Change `getOduByName` to return mapped data from ODUS_IFA\nB. Make `OduData` shape compatible with ODUS_IFA and remove the duplicate fields\n\nLet me see what fields of `OduData` are used by `glossary.ts`:\n- `name` → `oduName`\n- `essencia` → `essencia`\n- `quizilas[0]` → `quizila`\n- `preceitos[0]` → `conselho`\n\nThat's it. Only 4 fields used. The OduData interface has 9 fields, and `getOduByName` returns null.\n\nThe cleanest surgical fix:\n- Modify `getOduByName` in `domain/odu-data.ts` to look up real Odu data from `ODUS_IFA` and return a mapped `OduData` object\n- Don't touch the OduData interface (consumers don't need to change)\n- The `domain/glossary.ts` will then work correctly without modification\n- Update `application/akasha/glossary.ts` to also import from the canonical source\n\nLet me also check the canonical source naming vs OduData name:\n- ODUS_IFA name: 'Ogbe (Oxé)' (with parenthetical)\n- The function will be called with name from odu.oduName: e.g. 'Ogbe (Oxé)'\n\nI need name normalization: strip parentheticals, lowercase comparison, then map back.\n\nActually, let me just make the lookup simpler. The `ODUS_IFA` names like \"Ogbe (Oxé)\" can be looked up by partial match. Let me write a helper that takes the name and returns a real Odu data.\n\nBut wait — the Pilar 4 invariant (AGENTS.md §5) says I must derive, not invent. The `ODUS_IFA` data is itself derived from `IDEIA.md §5` (canonical). So this satisfies the invariant.\n\nLet me also look at what the file should be:","signature":"22c3381c324ee66cd172d9cfe9de6cdc801a42412fc1227efec56362342f0bbf"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efa9633d-4bd4-4eaf-8cc7-696bf2eda76b","uuid":"2343358e-0e69-4dce-8299-2e13fda0de7f"}
