ve it use the same logic) — this removes the duplicate stub\n3. Add a test that verifies real data is returned for `Ogbe (Oxé)`\n4. Verify triad\n5. Commit + lesson\n\nWait, looking at the AGENTS.md rule more carefully: \n> \"nunca inventar correspondências esotéricas. Sempre derive from the canonical `CORRELATION_MAP`\"\n\nThe `ODU_DATABASE` in `domain/odu-data.ts` is itself derived from tradition (the file says \"Fonte: tradição nagô-yorubá (Ilé-Ifé). REGRA CRÍTICA: apenas dados verificáveis da tradição. Nenhuma invenção.\"). So it's a derivation of canonical knowledge, not invention. Good.\n\nLet me also check: should I delete `application/akasha/glossary.ts` or just delegate it to domain/glossary? Let me look at the imports more carefully — they're two separate concerns:\n- `domain/glossary.ts` — for IA prompt injection (consult route)\n- `application/akasha/glossary.ts` — for daily-engine + manifesto-builder\n\nBoth serve the same purpose. The cleanest fix: make `application/akasha/glossary.ts` re-export from `domain/glossary.ts`. That removes the duplicate stub without breaking consumers.\n\nBut this might break the import path. Let me see what the import looks like in daily-engine:\n```typescript\nimport { buildOduGlossary, formatGlossarySection } from './glossary';\n```\n\nThat relative path is `apps/akasha-portal/src/lib/application/akasha/glossary.ts`. If I make it re-export from domain, the consumers won't change.\n\nPlan:\n1. Fix `domain/odu-data.ts` `getOduByName` to handle parenthetical names (strip `(...)` and re-lookup)\n2. Replace `application/akasha/glossary.ts` body with re-export from `domain/glossary.ts`\n3. Add test in `tests/lib/akashic/` for `buildOduGlossary` and `getOduByName`\n4. Verify typecheck + tests\n5. Commit + lesson\n\nLet me also check: does the input name from chart.oduBirth.oduName actually contain `(Oxé)`? Let me check odu-birth.ts again:\n- Line 49: `oduName: odu.nome` where `odu.nome = 'Ogbe (Oxé)'` (from ODUS_IFA)\n\nYes, the input is \"Ogbe (Oxé)\" not \"Ogbe\". This is the bug.\n\nWait — but D-044 F1 said \"IFA_ODUS tem 15 (não 16) — Eji substitui Ogbe por design Phase 1\". So Pilar 4 canonical list excludes Ogbe. But the `domain/odu-data.ts` has Ogbe. The `ODUS_IFA` (from core-odus) has Ogbe (Oxé). So they're consistent in having Ogbe.\n\nThe bug is just the lookup. Let me fix it.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, this is a great F-219:\n- 1 file change for the bug fix (1-3 lines in `getOduByName`)\n- 1 file change for the de-dup (replace body of `application/akasha/glossary.ts`)\n- 1 new test file\n- Total: 3 files, ~50-100 LOC\n- Real value: LLMs now receive real Odu context instead of nothing\n\nLet me start. First, check what tests exist for these:","signature":"cf6fc899a192fe85719df22f7417cc6cdb843ba28b175f3de6cca264dab7f102"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efa9633d-4bd4-4eaf-8cc7-696bf2eda76b","uuid":"fdb37294-a8b9-4bd7-9599-f558bad79620"}
